  "tabs": [
    {
      "name": "Main",
      "gid": "1923267969",
      "row_count": 5,
      "data_row_count": 0,
      "headers": [
        "Welcome to RotomAmiti's Cameo Pokémon Card Database! What is this? What is this for? How do I use this database? ",
        "This sheet is a listing of every time a Pokémon appears on a card that does not have its name. Well-known examples include the Natu on Legendary Treasures Bouffalant or the Weedle on Base Set Scoop Up. The sheet is intended to help collectors of specific Pokémon species locate cards where their target is not the cards' main focus. This sheet's tabs are organized into each Generation of Pokémon, plus an additional tab for humans labeled \"Trainers\". Go to the tab corresponding to the Pokémon you're looking for. For example, if you want cards with Wingull, go to Gen 3. Alternate forms are included alongside the original. Human characters listed in the Trainers tab are ordered by region of appearance, and then grouped somewhat arbitrarily within those regions. Generic Trainer classes are at the end. Cards displayed in Italics indicate that the Pokémon is an edge case. The Pokémon may not be entirely in frame, or may be represented by a toy or costume. The Notes column will indicate what is specifically going on. Cards displayed with a light blue background indicate the card was never released in English. If the card was not released in Japanese either, then the language it is available in will be indicated in the Notes column. Card names that are in merged cells indicate that the set numbers all correspond to the same artwork. ",
        "",
        "",
        "",
        "What is included on this list? What is not included on this list? ",
        "Every officially-printed, standard-sized card that includes a Pokémon not in the card's name is eligible for the list. There are many cases where the Pokémon is not physically present, such as a toy or silhouette; these are included for the sake of completion. All Trainer cards that have Pokémon on the artwork are included, whether the Pokémon is in the name of the card or not. Human characters function somewhat inversely to Pokémon. Any Trainer card that does not include the character's name is listed, plus every Pokémon card whether the character is in the name or not. This is because Trainer cards almost always feature the named character, but the Trainer's Pokémon mechanic does so suprisingly rarely. Jumbo-only cards are included. They have \"Jumbo\" noted in the Notes column. The original version of this sheet did not include Jumbos, but they have since been added. This list focuses on English releases, and with some exceptions, every English release of any particular card is included. Unique releases in other languages are also included, once. The sheet is currently up-to-date with all English releases up to and including Chaos Rising, and all Japanese releases up to and including Ninja Spinner. By and large, \"symbiotic\" Pokémon are not included. Drakloak cards are not listed as appearances by Dreepy beacuse every Drakloak includes a Dreepy anyway. Pokémon that only appear on stamps, such as the Pikachu from the English 25th Anniversary Promos, are not included. The nature of stamps mean that some prints of these cards may not include them, and they aren't part of the card's artwork regardless. Human characters that only appear in infoboxes such as those on Trainer's Pokémon and Pokémon SP are not included."
      ],
      "csv_hash": "5a9810ac5516792139e05580b5236e7c0bb6275fb7923fc9b4f49cdcd9cfd476"
